Explanation of Lead Statuses & How Users Use Them

I’ve added customizable statuses to help users track leads through different sales stages. Here’s what each new status does and how users can use them:

1. Negotiation

Purpose:

  • This status is for leads that are actively discussing pricing, contracts, or terms before making a final decision.

How to Use:

  • When a lead expresses serious interest but needs more details, move them to "Negotiation."
  • Use this status to track leads that require discount offers, contract reviews, or competitor comparisons.
  • Add notes about what was discussed and schedule a follow-up call or meeting to finalize the deal.

✅ Example:

  • A company is interested in buying 500 test kits, but they need a bulk discount. Move them to Negotiation while you prepare a custom quote.

2. Closed Won

Purpose:

  • This status is for leads that have successfully converted into customers and completed a purchase.

How to Use:

  • When a lead makes a payment or places an order, change their status to "Closed Won."
  • Keep a record of order details and follow up with post-sale engagement (e.g., send an email thanking them and offering reorders).
  • Track the total number of "Closed Won" leads to measure sales success.

✅ Example:

  • A rehab center purchases 1,000 drug test cups after a negotiation. Update their status to Closed Won and send them a follow-up email.

3. Closed Lost

Purpose:

  • This status is for leads that decided not to purchase or are no longer interested.

How to Use:

  • When a lead explicitly declines the offer or chooses another vendor, change their status to "Closed Lost."
  • Use this status to track why leads were lost (price, competitors, timing issues, etc.).
  • Set a reminder to check back in a few months in case their situation changes.

✅ Example:

  • A staffing agency decides to go with a competitor's test kits. Move them to Closed Lost but schedule a follow-up in 6 months to check if they reconsider.

How Users Interact with Statuses in the CRM

  1. Changing Statuses:
    • Users can select a lead's status from the dropdown menu when they move through the sales process.
  2. Filtering Leads:
    • Users can filter leads by status (e.g., only show Negotiation leads) to focus on high-priority deals.
  3. Tracking Performance:
    • Users can see how many leads convert to Closed Won vs. Closed Lost and adjust their sales strategy.

import { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { Table } from "@/components/ui/table";

export default function CRMApp() {
const [leads, setLeads] = useState([]);
const [newLead, setNewLead] = useState({ name: "", contact: "", phone: "", email: "", followUpDate: "", notes: "", activityLog: [], score: 0 });
const [searchQuery, setSearchQuery] = useState("");

useEffect(() => {
const checkFollowUps = () => {
const today = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0];
leads.forEach(lead => {
if (lead.followUpDate === today) {
alert(`Reminder: Follow up with ${lead.name} today!`);
}
});
};
checkFollowUps();
}, [leads]);

const addLead = () => {
setLeads([...leads, { ...newLead, id: Date.now(), status: "New" }]);
setNewLead({ name: "", contact: "", phone: "", email: "", followUpDate: "", notes: "", activityLog: [], score: 0 });
};

const updateLeadStatus = (id, status) => {
const updatedLeads = leads.map(lead => {
if (lead.id === id) {
if (status === "Follow-up") {
sendAutomatedEmail(lead.email);
}
return { ...lead, status };
}
return lead;
});
setLeads(updatedLeads);
};

const sendAutomatedEmail = (email) => {
console.log(`Sending automated email to ${email} with follow-up details.`);
// This is where email API integration would be implemented (e.g., SendGrid, Mailgun)
};

const filteredLeads = leads.filter(lead =>
lead.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchQuery.toLowerCase()) ||
lead.contact.toLowerCase().includes(searchQuery.toLowerCase()) ||
lead.phone.includes(searchQuery) ||
lead.email.toLowerCase().includes(searchQuery.toLowerCase())
);

return (
<div className="p-4 bg-[#F5F5F5] min-h-screen">
<h1 className="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-[#0073E6]">Simple CRM</h1>
<Card className="p-4 mb-4 shadow-lg bg-white rounded-lg border border-[#0073E6]">
<h2 className="text-lg font-semibold text-[#0073E6]">Add New Lead</h2>
<div className="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-2">
<Input className="border-[#0073E6]" placeholder="Business Name" value={newLead.name} onChange={(e) => setNewLead({ ...newLead, name: e.target.value })} />
<Input className="border-[#0073E6]" placeholder="Contact Person" value={newLead.contact} onChange={(e) => setNewLead({ ...newLead, contact: e.target.value })} />
<Input className="border-[#0073E6]" placeholder="Phone Number" value={newLead.phone} onChange={(e) => setNewLead({ ...newLead, phone: e.target.value })} />
<Input className="border-[#0073E6]" placeholder="Email" value={newLead.email} onChange={(e) => setNewLead({ ...newLead, email: e.target.value })} />
<Input className="border-[#0073E6]" type="date" placeholder="Follow-Up Date" value={newLead.followUpDate} onChange={(e) => setNewLead({ ...newLead, followUpDate: e.target.value })} />
</div>
<Button className="mt-2 bg-[#0073E6] text-white hover:bg-[#005bb5]" onClick={addLead}>Add Lead</Button>
</Card>
<Table className="bg-white shadow-lg rounded-lg border border-[#0073E6]">
<thead>
<tr className="bg-[#FFD700] text-left">
<th className="p-2 text-left">Business</th>
<th className="p-2 text-left">Contact</th>
<th className="p-2 text-left">Phone</th>
<th className="p-2 text-left">Email</th>
<th className="p-2 text-left">Status</th>
<th className="p-2 text-left">Follow-Up Date</th>
<th className="p-2 text-left">Actions</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
{filteredLeads.map((lead) => (
<tr key={lead.id} className="border-b border-[#0073E6] text-left">
<td className="p-2 text-[#0073E6]">{lead.name}</td>
<td className="p-2 text-[#0073E6]">{lead.contact}</td>
<td className="p-2 text-[#0073E6]">{lead.phone}</td>
<td className="p-2 text-[#0073E6]">{lead.email}</td>

<td className="p-2 flex space-x-2">
<Button className="bg-[#FFD700] text-white hover:bg-[#ccac00]" onClick={() => updateLeadStatus(lead.id, "Follow-up")}>Follow-up</Button>
<Button className="bg-[#00A859] text-white hover:bg-[#007a43]" onClick={() => updateLeadStatus(lead.id, "Ready")}>Ready</Button>
<Button className="bg-[#FF8C00] text-white hover:bg-[#cc6d00]" onClick={() => updateLeadStatus(lead.id, "Negotiation")}>Negotiation</Button>

))}
